text: The Toulouse Hawks are an Australian rules football team based in Toulouse, France. As of 2018, the team primarily competes in the national competitions in France including the Championnat de France and the French Cup. The team typically wears black and white jumpers. == History == Originally formed in 2008 as the Toulouse Crocodiles, the Toulouse Hawks first competed in the Championnat de France in the 2009/2010 season, finishing 3rd overall. The club would go on to win the league in the 2012/2013 and 2013/2014 seasons as well as the 2010 and 2015 editions of the French Cup.
